What is happening here:
+ **Line 5** executes the `new` operator. It's result (memory address of the array) is stored in the `EAX` register (mostly `EAX` is used for returning values)
+ **Line 6** inserts `1` into the memory. The address is in `EAX`. Every managed object in .NET has some metadata. In this case the first 8 bytes are reserved for metadata. Position `0` in the array would be `[eax + 8]`

